  "title": "Sales Manager (Semiconductor Components)",
  "description": "<p><strong>Sales Manager (Semiconductor Components)</strong></p><p><strong>Key Responsibilities:</strong></p><ul><li>Achieve revenue targets for assigned accounts and market segments.</li><li>Manage the end-to-end sales process, including RFQs, pricing, and negotiations.</li><li>Act as the primary point of contact for major customers and distributors on all issues.</li><li>Represent customer requirements to internal teams (production, operations, quality, and management) to ensure effective, customer-first solutions.</li><li>Build and manage strong relationships with key accounts, internal stakeholders (HQ, regional, and U.S. sales teams), and distribution partners.</li><li>Conduct regular business reviews with customers and partners to strengthen engagement and alignment.</li><li>Identify new business opportunities through market research and competitive analysis.</li><li>Collaborate with product managers and cross-functional teams to drive mutual growth and profitability.</li><li>Prepare and present weekly and monthly sales reports to management.</li></ul><p><strong>Qualifications & Requirements:</strong></p><ul><li>Bachelor's degree in Electronics, Electrical Engineering, or Business Administration.</li><li>Proven track record in sales & marketing of semiconductors or components.</li><li>Extensive knowledge of the electronics industry in South East Asia is desirable.</li><li>Minimum of 5 years of relevant experience.</li></ul><p></p>",
